race.description: Ladbrokes 55 Second Challenge Series 1 Final Hcp  (Bm74)
race.comment: Over to the 955m final and FIELDELO (11) looks the one to beat. She won her first two starts impressively, bolting in over 10000m at Bendigo by seven lengths at her second outing before acquitting herself well in strong 3yo company over the Winter, just missing in a Listed race before a spell. The 955m here is a different challenge but on ability, she should go close. SHIRSHOV (1) tried hard behind a dominant winner in Beast Mode around here last time who won in very fast time. The effort to hold on for second reads well and he'll land in a good spot. Wary of POWER OF THE BRAVE (3) who won well over 900m at Newcastle as favourite first up. He's clearly very speedy and can measure up. ONE HARD LADY (10) was a narrow heat winner here first up and has to be respected with improvement to come. MIDNIGHT DEVIL (9) was good last time and is in the mix.
